	<p class="subhead" id="Dinner"><img src="images/SMTurtle.jpg" class="li-turtle tilt" alt="turtle" />99th Annual Lodge Dinner <span class="label label-success">New</span></p>
	<p>The new year is just around the corner, and with it comes the annual lodge dinner. This dinner is one of the more popular events of the year, where awards are distributed including the Founders Award, Oustanding Service Awards, and Chuck Benshetler Spirit of Camp Leadership Award. The fun doesn't stop there, as this is the same event where the State of the Lodge is delivered, the new officers are inducted and many other lodge and national events are announced. This is also one of our events where the whole family is invited; guests don't need to belong to the O.A. or scouting. Officers from surrounding lodges, the section, region, and even national have been in attendance, so you might as well join them! You can <a href="http://colbsa.doubleknot.com/event/2015-lodge-annual-dinner/1595021" target="_blank">register online now</a>! Make sure you register by December 26, because after that a $5 late fee will be added on to each person.</p>

	<p class="subhead" id="Fall_Fellowship"><img src="images/SMTurtle.jpg" class="li-turtle tilt" alt="turtle">Fall Fellowship</p>
	<p>This past weekend sure was exciting as brothers from all over the Lodge came together to compete in the Highland Games and perform service for their fellow scouts. In the coming days, Photos will be uploaded to our <a href="http://www.facebook.com/unamione" target="_blank">Facebook Page</a> and <a href="photos">Photos Page</a>, so make sure you stay tuned! As for now, the winners of the election and your 2015 centennial executive officers is listed below. Below that, you can find the slideshow from this past weekend.</p>
	<p>We look forward to seeing you at the Annual Lodge Dinner in January! For a complete list of the projects completed, check it out on the <a href="communications-serviceupdate">Service Update Page</a>.</p>
